Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.63,0:00:54.56,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Ippei Yasuda inauguration party
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.56,0:00:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, congratulations, Mr. Yasuda!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.96,0:01:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But like a true maverick{as well as you are}, your offspring{son} ended up getting employed at such a peculiar place!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.54,0:01:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is, indeed, such a headache{nuisance}. This fellow has no idea what he got involved into.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.44,0:01:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The 53rd{Might be 93rd} {Prime}Minister Mr. Shibata is attending as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.85,0:01:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing compared to General Secretary Kawamura \Nor Yamazaki of the Fukuyama Domain. {I'm not sure here, it may also be 'aka' instead of 'or'}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.48,0:01:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But what a first class party it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.09,0:01:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet! No wonder since this is a party for the successor of Yasuda Inc{Zaibatsu}, estimated first or second in Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.01,0:01:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.88,0:01:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Grandfather Honda...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.95,0:01:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking for you since a while ago. \NBut I still don't seem to find Ippei.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too pompous. He'd never attend such an inflated party on a mere occasion of his inauguration.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.53,0:02:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad, too bad.{That's unfortunate.} The party of this scale is incomplete without him.{is a sight to behold.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that the time has come for him to leave the nest.{to become a full-fledged adult.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.70,0:02:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By any chance, can this person be the{Japan} Business Federation chairman Honda?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.70,0:02:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable how even his fiancee is among the invited guests!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.29,0:02:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitomi Misaki. There.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.50,0:02:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Her domain spans from Japan's political and business world to the world of yakuza.{She is a central figure everywhere - from the political and business circles of Japan to yakuza's world.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.25,0:02:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder for the Old Man of Northeast's{Tohoku} granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.48,0:02:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So she is the sole heir to all the political{influence} and financial power{assets} of this old man, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.98,0:02:37.05,Default,SIGN,0,0,45,,{\fs50\fade(0,700)\bord0\shad3\blur1\c&H4E42F2&\4c&H000027&}M{\c&H4A42F1&}y{\c&H4742EF&} {\c&H4342EE&}s{\c&H4043ED&}k{\c&H3C43EB&}i{\c&H3843EA&}e{\c&H3543E8&}s{\c&H3143E7&} \N\N\N{\fs30\c&HE7F7F7&\4c&H020406&\3c&H000000&}Criminal{Detective} chapter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.94,0:02:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Station calling Kyobashi vehicle 3-5{, over}. {Half-guessing here, can't hear a thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.18,0:02:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Kyobashi 3-5 copy, over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Investigate the young woman body in the river as soon as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.21,0:02:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger that, will do right away. \NOn the way to the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.82,0:03:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Kyobashi, do you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.33,0:03:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be a suicide. No signs of a violent death. It does not look like a homicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.51,0:03:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so, huh? Still, it feels like something's off{wrong}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.07,0:03:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably was a pretty lass, though. Did you see the face?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.13,0:03:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame her time was so short.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.55,0:03:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A young and pretty lady, she doesn't seem to have reasons to commit suicide in the middle of night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.71,0:03:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only speak for yourself. Life is a zebra. Even for the pretty ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.96,0:03:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You were in the lounge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.79,0:03:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The atmosphere was not to my taste. {I didn't like it down there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.40,0:03:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{Unlike them, }I see no issue in{I have no objections against} Ippei{you} becoming a police officer{to make a fuss about it}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.47,0:03:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you are to become a police officer... I want you to be a police officer only you can be. {I want you to remain your current self even when you become a police officer.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.45,0:04:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight's party served the same purpose.{was also organized with the intention of conveying to you this idea.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.41,0:04:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.78,0:04:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I use this hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.66,0:04:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's much more convenient than going to work from Yasuda residence. {The Yasuda residence is located less convenient for going anywhere and coming back.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.71,0:04:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure at what time I will be leaving and returning home from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.60,0:04:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can no longer operate under the Yasuda umbrella. {Being covered by Yasuda umbrella is no longer exusable for me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free to use it however you please. Forget that it belongs to me, it belongs to you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.76,0:04:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.29,0:04:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective Tamura, your tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.16,0:04:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You think now's the time for tea parties?!{It's not the case for something like tea drinking!} Take it{the hell} away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.03,0:04:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you waiting for{dumbfounded}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.57,0:04:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have nothing else to do, start swabbing the toilets! {Lit: If you are a rookie with a free time, consider cleaning the restroom!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.58,0:04:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.04,0:05:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, Tamura. I can understand your frustration{feelings}, but such is our line of work. {but a case is a case.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.03,0:05:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In spite of all our efforts, we have close it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of untimely demise is too miserable for such a beauty!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.02,0:05:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The deceased was a youthful lass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we... Are we really going to bargain with such bastards? {Is it... It is really what we will present to our colleagues?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we look our families in the eyes after that?! {How will we look them[our colleagues (from previous alternative line]) in the eyes after that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.36,0:05:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we call this a suicide? The woman was clearly murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.37,0:05:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have to give up without even trying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.04,0:05:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Following the example of the pile of previous girls, the case has been issued a Stop command.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.17,0:05:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.25,0:05:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They say she was a girl of easy virtue{a flighty streetwalker}. Ended up being kidnapped by a gang of kid bikers{bosozoku}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.05,0:05:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what? {And after that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.42,0:05:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, those kids ended her life, one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.56,0:05:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them turned out to be the younger son of Yotaro Atagawa, the Minister of Health.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.54,0:05:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they just sealed it off with "suicide."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.52,0:06:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In exchange for{And the bargaining chip was} director's promotion, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.92,0:06:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, trainee! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To enforce the law upon Atagawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You do understand that will be the end of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.15,0:06:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stir up that case{hornet's nest}, you will be out of detectives before new year's eve! {early in the new year!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.33,0:06:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not joking. {This is not a joke.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.64,0:06:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,To catch a scoundrel that is ought to be caught, one doesn't have to be a detective or anything of the kind. {If I can't even catch a guy who has to be caught, then I don't want all this detective regalia at all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You do not seem to have heard me well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This case{incident} has to be closed{is resolved}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened is nothing but a corny suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.47,0:06:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a wretched girl, unwilling to take part in marriage of convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.85,0:07:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, since you already came here{you've already went through the effort of coming here}, this is for the two of you — a compensation for the taxi ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Naito from the Ministry of Social Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.31,0:07:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that you, Mr. Naito? I have a remarkable story{rumour / news / evidence} for you. {I have a fine gossip to shed light on.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.21,0:07:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Minister of Health son... That's right. Yoichiro Atagawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.17,0:07:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- How dare you! \N- The deal with him is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, his courage is in a bit of decline.{he lacks any guts to face justice.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Asshole, what are you trying to pull...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.98,0:07:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while, sorry to interrupt your vacation. Ippei talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.11,0:07:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one fellow that'd like to have a little talk. Will pass the phone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.12,0:07:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Atagawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.59,0:07:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Such a... Such a ridiculous thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.90,0:08:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was it you called back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.80,0:08:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Issei Wakabayashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wakabayashi is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.79,0:08:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.95,0:08:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing special.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.88,0:08:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You turned out to be a resourceful one... {I wonder how many approaches are open to you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.70,0:08:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{Pure [Shochu]}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.70,0:08:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, did you not have enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.59,0:08:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say stupid! Today your successful detective career has started! {you have closed your first brilliant case!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.74,0:08:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to celebrate it. Get filthy drunk! Have fun!{Do it!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.77,0:08:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn right around this corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.81,0:08:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.11,0:09:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, that's the place. Gramps! How is it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it is kingpin{my favourite customer \ master \ any distinguished person, endowed with power and influence in criminal world} Tamura who is asking, then it's going swimmingly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Gramps, don't blend our shochu tonight. We will only drink{pure} rock-hard {top-}branded one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.53,0:09:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This fella's first success has to be commemorated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood! Rock-hard one it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'll go take a quick piss.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.74,0:09:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Not!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave me be! {Let me go!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.39,0:09:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not trying to take anything away from you. See, baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, you backstreet cockroach.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.61,0:09:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you just mutter something to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.05,0:09:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Merely said you're a backstreet cockroach.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.65,0:09:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.55,0:09:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You deaf? {Should I repeat?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn jackass, you're not getting away with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.64,0:09:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You're fucking noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.44,0:09:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a Marubo henchman? {丸暴 - regular police department, dealing with organized crime and mobsters, often using the yakuza methods against yakuza}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.88,0:09:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut the fuck up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.82,0:10:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloody prick... What did I ever do to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.85,0:10:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens next, depends on this mechanism's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.19,0:10:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too nervous{easily excited \ emotional} for a chinpira.{チンピラ - a petty wannabe yakuza, typically a delinquent, trying to appear an actual mobster but lacking guts of one}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A pistol? Hey! What kind of mobster skirmish is that?{I don't like where this is going!} Quit it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.16,0:10:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,None of your business! {I'll handle this myself!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.39,0:10:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Ippei?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.95,0:10:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You picked the wrong people to fool around with!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.83,0:10:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, isn't it Tamura from Kyobashi Dept?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.96,0:10:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Mr. Komiya...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.88,0:10:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that kid is also a minion{henchman} for your office?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.86,0:10:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.37,0:10:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yakuza and detectives have one thing in common - if you ever see one, get out the way. {Yakuza and detectives use similar methods. If you can't stomach going to the extremes, you better resign. - I }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yakuza are also people! The way you treated him right now is totally unacceptable!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.27,0:10:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, are you trying to sermonize me? Kyobashi rookie training program sucks hard, it seems!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.70,0:11:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamura, I caught this man molesting a girl. Detain him to see if there are other sins to his name.{to check what else is there in his bio.}{to add that to his record.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.14,0:11:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that ruffian?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.51,0:11:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss of Marubo, Field Officer Komiya from the main office{department}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.73,0:11:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Their department deals with the organized crime. And no one does it better than this astounding man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.88,0:11:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If Mr. Komiya bothered to kick his ass, there must be some reason. That man has to have his hands dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.44,0:11:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon my lateness. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.59,0:11:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sorry we had to wake you early in the morning. {sorry we interrupted your day off.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.91,0:11:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No, work comes first for me. {Work is the first priority for me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.44,0:11:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of some prejudices, the guy from Nakano{yesterday} remains completely tongue-tied round the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.38,0:11:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to approach him as well, but to no avail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.88,0:11:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, recently he yielded to crack if we call up that young handsome detective to handle him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Yasuda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the deal with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.58,0:12:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You are one of those geta-faced thickskulls!{Your face looks like a geta!}{'Geta-headed' - dim and unappealing person, typically a yakuza cooperator / police despot, seeking to abuse his authority i.e. 'the bad cop' -> hence the Nakano guy repulsuion for Tamura} Get the fuck out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.64,0:12:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you think you are!? {What did you just say?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.08,0:12:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I only agreed to spill it to the young one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.95,0:12:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen yourself how obstinately tight-lipped I can be while seeing some bulky face around! {We had a deal that I only open my mouth in absence of some big-mouthed blockhead like you!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.01,0:12:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You!{Asshole!} What kind of big shot do you think you are to keep barking like that!? {For someone slandering other's mouths, you don't seem to have a lot of knack at using yours!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The interrogations are supposed to be conducted by two!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.81,0:12:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{Go ahead, }Do it your way and you're getting nothing out of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.45,0:12:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You dare...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.74,0:12:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's fine... I'll try to somehow do it by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.35,0:12:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Bullshit! {What the heck!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.34,0:12:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, the getaheads confronted me with my previous criminal record, neatly arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.81,0:12:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There was but one skeleton in the cupboard they omitted.{There was just one thing they didn't know about.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.84,0:12:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What{ is it}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In Toyama, it makes three chicks this year. {Lit: The number of child girls [missing\dead] has already risen to three in Toyama in current year.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But a way out that I could see in your eyes... {In your eyes, I could see it's about time I clean up my act [because I'm sufficiently mature now].}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.43,0:12:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is your unspoiled{idealistic / pure} spirit. {Your uncorrupted-ness prompted me to do so.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.73,0:13:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What I saw in those eyes... {When I looked in those eyes,}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.01,0:13:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was a sharp recollection of all the poor girls. {the memories of unfortunate girls were suddenly brought back to life.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I will return to my hometown{[in the countryside]}, start the life from the scratch once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.20,0:13:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A rape show? {the way he pronounces it, this line sounds very close to 'Return to hometown?', but with his reaction, 'rape show' seems more appropriate}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy from Nakano decided to clean his conscience{[with a farewell gift]} before stepping off the slippery slope{turning over a new leaf}{Lit: 'Decided to wash his feet with some parting souvenirs.' -> therefore I try to preserve some allusion to legs and cleaning}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.06,0:13:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A rape show in Ikebukuro, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, the number of{ cases of} college girls{female university students} going missing in this area is abnormally high.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.99,0:13:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! This is a case for the Field Officer Komiya from the main department! {Call Chief Komiya from the main department!}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.68,0:13:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kaisei{-kai = group} Group{Syndicate} is rapidly consolidating its power in the Johoku district.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.86,0:13:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt that their prime funding source is this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.90,0:13:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The rape show is being held in the Matsuba Motel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.73,0:13:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Overnight, it yields them about 300 000 000 yen or even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.55,0:13:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, in regards to the rape show itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.06,0:13:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Some way or another, they kidnap college girls and even female office workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.48,0:14:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bound by any reservations, they proceed straight to the improvisation. {Everything is devoted to the goal of convincing acting / performance. They begin the spectacle without any rehearsals at all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.22,0:14:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{After each show, the innocent girl that was used for it, is considered spent.} {During the show, an oblivious young lady is being used for one and only occasion ever.} For this show, they use unsuspecting girls, each one not more than once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.64,0:14:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Among spectators, there are even those who crave to perform a rape upon a defenseless{exhausted} girl{ then}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The suburbs of Tokyo harbor way too many cases of female students suddenly going missing. {This account for abnormally high occurence of female students going missing without a reason in Tokyo outskirts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.26,0:14:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They are probably being used not only for the duration of the rape show but afterwards as well. {There's a chance the missing girls remain in 'use' both during the show and after it is over.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the next show will be held next Sunday, on 24th!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.19,0:15:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Impressive, isn't it? Such operation with just 20 people!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.20,0:15:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing special.{No wonder. \ It's his common practice.} Mr. Komiya always means business. {If Komya is leading it, everyone is earnest.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.22,0:15:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This operation is supposed to be a joint enterprise of the Main office, {us }Kyobashi and of course, {the crime scene }Ikebukuro departments.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.53,0:15:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's about all I got to comment on everyone's mission{assignment}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, chief of staff Komiya will provide you with a terse briefing. {At this point, I am giving the floor to chief of staff Komya for a word of guidance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.83,0:15:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The opponent is the yakuza{Aiming for the most general sense here. This one is very ambiguous: https://jisho.org/search/%E6%A5%B5%E9%81%93} of Kaisei Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.42,0:15:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As you are well aware, their back appears to be at all times covered by a huge political party of their own{at their disposal}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.59,0:15:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears as well that this party controls us, the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.84,0:15:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we will remain steadfast, because we're the best, aren't we!? {Lit: However, because I only chose the best of the best here [in our headquarters], we will become the stronghold [of justice], are we not?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.77,0:15:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sending innocent girls straight to hell one after another with nothing but the sheer intention of making money is unforgivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.77,0:15:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right, people?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.47,0:15:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the motive is, such actions cannot be forgiven. It befalls on us to make them feel the consequences{isn't that so?}! {Let's make them take the full responsibility for their actions!} {Don't you think it is time we clean up that mess everyone was looking through fingers at?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.78,0:15:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we are the detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.20,0:15:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the {only}world you{we} happened to be living in!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people rejecting basic humanity{Again, ambiguous, aiming to generalize: http://www.romajidesu.com/dictionary/meaning-of-%E7%BE%A9%E7%90%86%E4%BA%BA%E6%83%85.html}, acting solely in their selfish{avaricious} interests!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no place for tears or hot-blooded considerations{compassion \ kindness: http://www.romajidesu.com/dictionary/meaning-of-%E8%A1%80%E3%82%82%E6%B6%99%E3%82%82%E3%81%AA%E3%81%84.html} when dealing with criminal organizations! Did I make myself clear?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.26,0:16:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Os! {Karate greet}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.22,0:16:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good job. Is Matsuba here?{Matsuba where?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.64,0:16:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He is waiting inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:29.63,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Kaisei Enterprise{Inc}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.66,0:16:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Bow!{Os!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.36,0:16:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Os!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.03,0:16:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.93,0:16:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to be working with you! {This should be another way of saying 'Well done!'}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.30,0:16:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please make yourself at home, bro{boss}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you done sorting out{procuring} the woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.56,0:16:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This time it's going swimmingly.{It's a fine one this time.} We nailed a superb belle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.46,0:16:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The show is supposed to be held tomorrow, on 24th... {So, the show is tomorrow, 24th...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.04,0:16:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But...? {Something wrong?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.50,0:16:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Komiya from Marubo. He has been acting funny lately. {He has become strangely active.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.52,0:16:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He may have got a leak{intel} about what we're up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.38,0:16:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He is scheming all year around, and you can't be constantly anxious about it. {Even if he'd try, you can't afford worrying about his activity forever.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.04,0:17:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, the cops have already busted one of our guys, and there's no chance he spills the beans. {It is almost a tliteral translation and still it feels he should be saying the opposite thing...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.66,0:17:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,First, think of our Kansai customers that have already hit the road and are on their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.64,0:17:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to cancel it now{ that it's underway}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.20,0:17:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, there's also my father with General Secretary Kawamura{Wft, this one attended Ippei's party} and Atagawa's second son, who we can show around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know what they can do to return the favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.58,0:17:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is that really so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that means we can proceed without worrying! {Well, that's a huge relief to know!} {They should be ushered in in a moment's notice then!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.54,0:17:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, please let me handle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.90,0:17:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.{If you say so.} Well, I entrust this to you. {Well, I'll let you handle it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.44,0:17:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight we act according to plan{schedule}. The bastards are holding the rape show.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.93,0:17:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, listen closely! We can't know for sure what is going on inside. {We have no way of seeing the moves of these guys inside the building.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.92,0:17:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The show begins at 23:00. It's 11 at night. {PM}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.36,0:17:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our deadline for storming the building is 11:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.07,0:17:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The department chief will instruct you on the scene layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.00,0:18:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I will need you to storm the crime scene simultaneously and without a delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.25,0:18:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hence, Field Officer Komiya will be in the vanguard, breaking the way through for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.52,0:18:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamura from Kyobashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Os!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as Mr. Honbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.55,0:18:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitagawa and Ishikawa from the Kyobashi Dept will go as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.51,0:18:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- OK!\N- Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Takei and Murata{There's no way to hear that surname clear thanks to the bloody sinth slam but it's of little importance anyway} from the Main Office will also join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.94,0:18:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Roger! \N- Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.81,0:18:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I will also require Sugiyama and Sakurai from Ikebukuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.44,0:18:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Roger! \N- Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.33,0:18:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, it is myself. There would be 9 of us — disguised and waiting patiently for the signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as we rush into the building, our standby agents will get into the position and block the rear exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:40.38,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Hotel \h                   \h Contruction works} 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.38,0:18:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The three remaining squads will secure the east{ side} completely. {I confess floating in this line; the 'sanpan' part may be another obscured slang}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.81,0:18:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone take a good look at this Matsuba motel sketch. Have it nailed firmly in your head! {Everyone memorize well that Matsuba motel sketch. Knock it into your skulls!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.57,0:18:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, the briefing is over. {That's about all.}Operation starts!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.17,0:19:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me, am I staying on the lookout again? {am I being overshadowed / overlooked again?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.06,0:19:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe such is fair to do?{I'm sorry, but how can you say so?} I was the first one to ever stumble upon{hear of} this case! {I was working on this case from the outset!}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.70,0:19:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a bit short on guts{muscle / experince / intellect} for that, Ippei. Someone has to stay on the lookout. {Staying on a lookout is an important job too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.35,0:19:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's fair? Such assignment is fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yasuda, let's take a walk. {Yasuda, let's have a talk.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.94,0:19:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh... Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.81,0:19:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Name is Mayumi Okawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.95,0:19:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yasuda, this is your tonight's companion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, listen closely. I need you two to become{transform into} a pair of lovebirds{Avec (Fr.) - passionate unreserved lovers} so as to infiltrate the Matsuba{ hotel}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.94,0:19:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As you have already grasped, we — the shock troops — will enter the building on your cue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.49,0:19:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone gives the game away{blows the cover}, the edge of shock troops perfect{precise} timing is scrapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.22,0:19:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll only catch small fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.41,0:19:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{Whether we attack or whether we wait more — everything is in the hands of the two of you. That's what I'm trying to say.} \NWhen to pull the trigger is up to you two. Everything depends on you. That's what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.15,0:19:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes. \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.04,0:20:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{I take it you know your ways with women.} You'd make a convincing Latin Lover{love interest hero / actor}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.75,0:20:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.26,0:20:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is still some time. Get along well and join us in the conference room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.87,0:20:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,L-Lovebirds then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.86,0:20:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I guess I should better let you change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.79,0:20:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.13,0:20:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, but aside from your company and a fancy tuxedo, Ms. Okawa...{[I will also require your love.]} {Unclear bc he might as well refer to Okawa's tuxedo but ultimately neither of them wears one; 'company' may also refer to the whole operation and not just the two of them}{'Bashi' or whatever that word is might as well mean smth like 'a bridge to you' instead of 'your company'}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.45,0:20:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What is on your mind at such a time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.47,0:20:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be on my mind at such a time. {Precicely because now is such a time, I have this on my mind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.43,0:20:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't make convincing enough lovebirds, we're busted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.39,0:20:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, I will be loving you with all sincerity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.86,0:20:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be so kind to love me reciprocally.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.72,0:20:53.70,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Hotel Matsuba
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.45,0:20:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsuba Motel is comprised by four aboveground floors and one underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.70,0:20:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The show is being held in the underground hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.21,0:21:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaisei group has one lookout at the front entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.15,0:21:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Two at the rear door.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.61,0:21:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Three more patrol the driveway to the motel from the Meiji-dori Avenue intersection.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.72,0:21:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the wiring is completely bare!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so! How does it look, can you fix it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.85,0:21:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll think of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.52,0:21:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, now's not the time to do the electrics maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.68,0:21:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like a power outage would be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.42,0:21:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to worry. Your side of the road is not connected to{affected by} this pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.23,0:21:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you need insulation fiber?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.77,0:21:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that'd come in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.40,0:21:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, okay? {Work well, man.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.33,0:21:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,East of the motel is the main boulevard. Roadworks. Four men, including Mr. Honbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.30,0:21:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Honbe, won't that look suspicious if you don't move{work} one bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.67,0:21:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It would take one an excessive mental effort to suspect someone with a face and appearance like mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.22,0:21:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if anything, such a face and appearance do not fit a general laborer{Literal would be 'civil servant' but I don't see a way to incorporate it in current context} as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:21:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't want to pick a fight with an oldster, that's for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.67,0:22:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,500 meters away from the motel, 13 more plainclothed detectives await orders in the microbus. {waiting standby in the microbus.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.37,0:22:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, 200 meters to the west, 30 more agents waiting for orders in a marked{police} truck{Lit: truck, bearing a company name.}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.37,0:22:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chef! Another guest has arrived{entered}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.58,0:22:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,With this one, it gives us a total of 38 guests. They just sealed the backdoor shutter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.72,0:22:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. This one was probably the last guest they are expecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.69,0:22:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Time?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.15,0:22:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,11:05.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.30,0:22:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, I've seen it just now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.23,0:22:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman and His Grace{Basically, any distinguished title will do. He just refers to someone important without specifying their role or position or relation to him aside from that they are being superior to him, like in 'August person,' e.g. minister, superintendent, director, gang leader, general secretary, sensei(lol), executive, CEO etc.} are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.15,0:22:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.54,0:22:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already waited until 11:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.46,0:22:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.40,0:22:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure everyone is on the edge of their seats about{twitching in excitement of} meeting{getting hands on} a young lady! {About time we show these days' youth how you put your back into making money!} {Very lousy since I'm uncertain about the 'ハルマン' part, my bet is 'getting a woman' or 'these days' in alternative line}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.11,0:22:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a single chance... A single chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.31,0:23:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.38,0:23:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,11:18.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.04,0:23:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Have those animals{brutes} already started?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.86,0:23:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This way please.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.47,0:23:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I{ have to} wait... here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.60,0:23:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fine lass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.99,0:23:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes to please Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We made sure to secure{arrange} an exclusive{special} belle for today's occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.31,0:23:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.89,0:23:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still too early. {It's not time yet.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.46,0:23:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we rush in{storm the place} before the show is on its peak, the whole game is down the drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Okawa, let me see your watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.49,0:23:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Too soon. Let's bide some more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.36,0:23:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Okawa, when did you graduate?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.09,0:23:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a part of the 45th generation{issue / edition / installment / vintage / graduation ceremony}, so it's last year's October.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.78,0:24:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out you are a mentor{senior} to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.41,0:24:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.19,0:24:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out,{It's dangerous,} the guard is coming. {ハルマン again, but my bet this time it's security guard}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.76,0:24:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Okawa, you{ truly} are astonishingly beautiful in your plain clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.07,0:24:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.99,0:24:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Brilliantly improvised.{A natural actor.} The guard{blockhead} totally bought it. {That rascal really is something.}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.15,0:24:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! What kind of place is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.91,0:24:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No... No!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.43,0:25:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No!!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.53,0:25:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,11:30. 15 minutes until the storm deadline. Let's go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.01,0:25:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They probably ordered the motel front desk to turn everyone away with{ something like} 'no vacancies.'{not let anyone enter with 'no vacancies' pretext.}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.38,0:25:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I will knock out the lookout to let you rush in all at once. {When that time comes, I will need you to storm the motel all at once, after I neutralize the guard.}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.42,0:25:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the fire alarm will go off. Start the storm on that signal. {This one is a bit tricky with tenses}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.64,0:26:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Please... Let me go! {Stop!}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.21,0:26:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He penetrated her!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.07,0:26:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm so sorry. We are totally out of vacancies today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.53,0:26:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?{I see.} Not gonna work?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.76,0:26:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The other hotel was also full to the brim.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.72,0:26:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if we wait here a bit... {You mind if we wait here for a bit?}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.16,0:26:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, like I said before...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.75,0:26:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that is just straight up rude{bad manners}, bro. Why don't you carry on outside, like you did before?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.10,0:26:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.54,0:26:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.32,0:26:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.91,0:27:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Okawa! Hit{Ring} the bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.79,0:27:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.11,0:27:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.74,0:27:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At last! Get em!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.59,0:27:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, the police is here! {oh fuck that scene, here goes nothing}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.81,0:27:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{Don't stop, don't stop, don't stop, don't stop!} Keep going going going going!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.56,0:27:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Outta my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.73,0:27:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't want us in!{We clearly are not welcome here!} Let's punch our way through!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.81,0:27:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{Assholes!}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.28,0:27:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They really are hiding something!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.58,0:27:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You have some guts, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.95,0:27:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.38,0:27:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The rear door is secured! Squad three and squad four join the assault!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.23,0:27:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{- Roger! \N- Roger!}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.02,0:27:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't fret! We can't let them in! {Go on, sue me for this line}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.86,0:28:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone freeze! Not a single bastard{body} moves!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.23,0:28:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all under arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.07,0:28:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll have our leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.16,0:28:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay where you are, you, on the balcony!{Stay still, everyone over there!}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.29,0:28:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And everyone who is with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.67,0:28:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Guests who just watched are arrested too! {Lit: Guests-observers are ordered to stay still!}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.30,0:28:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit pretending you didn't hear my order to stay still!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.60,0:28:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.37,0:28:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey!\N- Don't, Ippei!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.43,0:28:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Komiya!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.85,0:28:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Komiya...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.87,0:28:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Unforgivable...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.15,0:29:07.72,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Widespread{Large-scale} gang{syndicate} enforcement{coercion} investigations{inquiries}!! \N{Names of }11 Kaisei Group members arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.19,0:29:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with those newspapers? Not a word about the brutal rape show!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.31,0:29:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. First Investigation Dept.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.32,0:29:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.51,0:29:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.43,0:29:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ippei, where are you off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.79,0:29:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To meet Mr. Komiya. {Mr. Komiya called me for something.}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.32,0:29:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Yasuda came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.22,0:29:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.92,0:29:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to see you came, young man!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.48,0:30:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Those gentlemen are fourth investigation dept superintendent Keishi Kameda,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.38,0:30:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hidehisa Orei of the main{ police} office senior executives, {Don't look at me. No clue. I know there's no such a surname but I don't see a way to make this work otherwise. Komiya has a boner for regional accents and jargonisms which makes is utterly incomprehensible when coincides with him being drunk.}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.80,0:30:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally, the one sitting in the middle, is the renowned{distinguished} Congressman Mr. Ishioka. {He rather says 'Isshoukan' but I don't seem to find such a surname and will write it off to Komiya's intoxicated tongue again}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.37,0:30:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one{ of them} had his reputation publicly tarnished at least once. {Lit: Everyone is infamous for being exposed to public gaze hanging out in an unsavory company.}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.34,0:30:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, this applies to me as well. {Moreover, I was exposed this way as well.}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.16,0:30:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,These guys' word is the law to you. {These gentlemen entrust their skies to you.} {Oh well. Viva la freedom of interpretation, I guess.}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.94,0:30:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for giving us a positive answer anyway. {Thanks for complying with our little plea.}{doing us this little favour.} {This line will make sense later on, bear with me}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.78,0:30:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait just a moment more.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.44,0:30:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Komiya, what is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.77,0:30:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the newspapers...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.46,0:30:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing whatsoever concerning the brutal rape show.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.26,0:30:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Komiya, you don't say...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.66,0:30:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just the way life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.54,0:30:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the 22-agent investigation cannot alter the flow{way} of life. {'Sousai' may mean 'operation' as well as 'investigation' in this context}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.37,0:30:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you being pressured from above? They issue a Stop command to our investigation!?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.63,0:31:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this still a thing even to these days!? {Even now it is still a part and parcel of government work!?}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.46,0:31:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These guys put their own interests on the prime spot, above any laws and regulations. {For them, personal benefit / gain / enrichment / profit has the first priority, overshadowing even laws and moral principles.} {I've no clue if he refers to the guys present in the room or some other abstract cohort}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.80,0:31:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a thing... Why the hell were we even doing all of this? {Such inequity... For what goddamn purpose are we doing it then?}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.08,0:31:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you've had enough, Komiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.91,0:31:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to wait{, didn't I}...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.38,0:31:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I will cease{stop} the investigation like you told{ordered} me to. {The investigation will be closed in compliance with your decree.} {Your candid remark now was by all means righteous.} {There's a small chance he addresses Ippei, so I'll leave the second alt line here just in case}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.77,0:31:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But here, in private, I can personally give you just one possible answer{[to your request]}. {However, not for record, you have still not received an answer from me personally...}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.13,0:31:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So meet my answer! {And the answer is this!}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.48,0:31:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Komiya! What are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.64,0:31:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you out of your mind!?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.11,0:31:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing wrong with me! {Let me finish!} {No clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.65,0:31:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To your son of a bitch Congressman playing pet for his{ beloved} Grand Secretary, {Every move of your petty Congressman is the result of General Secretary pulling the strings!}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.76,0:31:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and to tame{chicken} underling "detectives" from the{ Metopolitan Police} Fourth Investigation Department, {And the underling Fourth Investigation Department is but the different chorus of the same song.}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.73,0:31:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the Komiya's answer! {Therefore this is my answer to them!}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.41,0:32:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Komiya was...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.50,0:32:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,reassigned{transferred} to a small island in the boondocks. {Look at Hitomi's legs lmao}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.43,0:32:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So he is a true castaway{island exile} now...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.56,0:32:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, tendering a resignation to turn a new leaf seems more favorable. {If it comes to that, I'd rather submit my resignation and start life anew.}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.56,0:32:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not so. Despite all of that, Mr. Komiya is still a police officer. A real{staunch / devoted} one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.12,0:32:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a real detective. He showed it to me. And he showed it to that man... {I've seen it myself. And that man had seen it too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.11,0:32:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the police then? What is public security?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.51,0:32:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{That was when}Therefore, I made up my mind about what I will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.76,0:32:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If a scoundrel has to be caught, I go and catch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.98,0:32:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If even the police itself is paid{bought} to become a hindrance to catching him, then I don't need it at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.69,0:32:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If catching a criminal requires money, any amount is worth it! {If you have to spend a fortune to catch a mobster, then spend it all you want!} {Any expenses are reasonable / justified when it comes / if it leads to catching a culprit!}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.33,0:32:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to catch that scoundrel, because he absolutely has to be caught! {We have to catch that scoundrel just for the sake of catching him!} {Sounds hypocritical but any other interpretation would be indecently liberal imo}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.95,0:32:55.48,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,{Concern}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.86,0:33:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot answer now. I told you not to call me for longer than five beeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.44,0:33:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought it's different for calls from Mr. Yasuda. {But it's a call from Mr. Yasuda, so I thought...}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.80,0:33:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then connect{put him through} at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.70,0:33:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, doing fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.21,0:33:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes... It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.33,0:33:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you busy tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.57,0:33:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? Why did you fall silent?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.03,0:33:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There is not a single thing more important to me now than all the newfound matters you have to tend to. {My utmost priority is not to distract you from all the important errands you now have.}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.95,0:34:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We're closing the case tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.39,0:34:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to dine with me tonight? A have a reserve at Princess of Hakone.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.79,0:34:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.79,0:34:26.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Omi Tunnel}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.09,0:34:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You have become a real{genuine} police officer, Ippei.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.66,0:34:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What you said back then, do you still feel that way about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.45,0:34:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still okay with{not opposed to} me becoming a cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.92,0:34:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,After becoming a cop, one suddenly stars being a target for all sorts of people. {Being a cop means having enemies of every imaginable kind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.98,0:35:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All I want is just to follow you wherever.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.24,0:35:27.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,Kyobashi Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.45,0:35:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.24,0:35:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, there are places way better than the office to spend midsummer in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.98,0:35:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.48,0:35:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Born in March of 1943{18th year of Showa}. Permanent residence in Okayama Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.42,0:35:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal file{ number} A14. {Suspected in }Two cases of murder{ through shooting}, five of blackmail.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.66,0:35:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Participation in organized crime: young successor{right hand man} of Kaisei Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.27,0:35:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose file do you have here?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.35,0:35:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoichi Toyoda's.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.13,0:35:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean Toyoda from the Kaisei Group?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.82,0:35:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.11,0:36:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Toyoda's record is not limited with a rape show organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.86,0:36:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This may allow us to corner{drive} Kaisei Group to liquidation{termination}.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.45,0:36:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Not happening. That son of a bitch Toyoda is too bright a smartass to let that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.54,0:36:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason he has not once revealed his true colors in all those years. {Up to this point, we never had him by the tail.}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.24,0:36:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not entirely so. With this, we should be able to take him down. {This oughta be enough to deal him a blow.}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.73,0:36:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.71,0:36:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Two years ago, Toyoda had a woman, Yasuko Ogura. Ultimately, she went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.76,0:36:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately after that, he married his current wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.52,0:36:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So what of that? {How does that help?}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.51,0:36:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is obviously Toyoda's work! I'll go out for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.80,0:36:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know where this is going, don't you, Mr. Honbe?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.80,0:36:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He is following Mr. Komiya's footsteps. {The same way Mr. Komiya did.}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.86,0:36:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing will come out of this. She just went missing with no loose ends. {There's nothing to work with. She just went missing, nothing else.}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.74,0:36:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If you say so. I will get to it right away.{I will go see what I can do at once.} Ippei's request?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.09,0:36:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.82,0:36:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard{got} you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.04,0:37:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going out. Bring a car to the front door at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.76,0:37:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up please.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.05,0:37:13.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Ozawa Cleaning Service\N... Restaurant}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.44,0:37:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{[Still unclear] Restaurant\NOzawa Cleaning Service}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.42,0:37:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, can I ask you a small favor? Which way is Shiro Sakaguchi's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.54,0:37:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{... Shop\NBar ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.37,0:37:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You want to hire me as a scout?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.68,0:37:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told you have a knack of obtaining miscellaneous intelligence. {That is quite literal, but maybe some kind of private detective synecdoche can do the trick better?}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.05,0:37:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that you make your living by getting the said intelligence. {And that you earn your living doing intelligence work.}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.44,0:37:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.03,0:37:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My special offer is a rate of 20 000 000 yen per year.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.67,0:37:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Additional 300 000 for each important piece of intelligence obtained.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.83,0:37:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, I will fully cover any expenses you incur while gathering the intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.82,0:38:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you also hire a{n undefined} number of intel gathering assistants, that would be dandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.89,0:38:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.74,0:38:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you even asking... what {\i1}I{\i0} say? {Why, instead of asking me... What do you say?}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.83,0:38:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{Mr?} Guchi, you weasel!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.23,0:38:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's way too much money!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.43,0:38:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought,{Told ya,} this lake is a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.45,0:38:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Visibility in the water is less than 2 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.69,0:38:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Algae growth is also present. No diver can operate in such conditions. {It renders diver operations completely out of question.} {Divers would have their hands completely tied in such a water.}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.47,0:38:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But you say that bastard Toyoda doused a woman in concrete and drowned her here?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.31,0:38:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it's just a hearsay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.95,0:38:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I'm screwed if I bring you a dummy{bust / soother / fraud}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.41,0:38:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lead{clue / story} from Ashiya{ city}. {This is a story from a reliable source.}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.23,0:39:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the kind of intel one shares with police{government}.{It's not the kind of info police gets from official sources.} This one is animate{alive}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.80,0:39:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon my candor, but the police is nowhere near as well aware as I am. {Sorry for being frank, but please don't even compare my leads to those of police.}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.55,0:39:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You distrust the most{only one} trustworthy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.95,0:39:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{It's what you chose yourself.} You will be treated the same way yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.85,0:39:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{Burns, burns!}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.74,0:39:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad,{However,} even if this is indeed the truth, you can see for yourself:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.47,0:39:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,our chances of raising the cadaver{drowned} from this water are 100% of failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.49,0:39:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The testimony worth nothing if he'll just dismiss it with an alibi. {No matter what testimony we provide because he can always just go ahead and arrange himself an alibi.}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.20,0:39:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is essential. We're not getting anywhere without it!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.18,0:39:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ippei, do you finally give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.01,0:39:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's but a first step towards crushing the Kaisei group.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.13,0:39:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Toyoda is the cornerstone of that citadel. {The linchpin of the whole structure is that Toyoda.}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.63,0:39:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to be caught by any means.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.72,0:39:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no going forward until Toyoda is caught, whatsoever. {Until Toyoda is caught by any means, there can be no future progress.}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.62,0:40:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitomi, please purchase about a square mile{ of land} from here to that mountain on the other side. {Hitomi, please buy the square mile around this mountain on the other side.} {Lit area would be '500 000 Tsubo' (坪 - about 3.3 m² each), equals to 1.65 kilometers², equals to 1.02 miles². I chose miles because it rounds up nicely.}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.95,0:40:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.38,0:40:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I will dam the valley, so we could bulldoze it{[the lake]}. {I will flood the valley and then bring bulldozers on site.}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.69,0:40:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Using the pumps, I will drain this lake dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.78,0:40:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What?{i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.72,0:40:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitomi, start the construction works tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.63,0:40:34.64,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Ippei Yasuda of Yasuda Conglomerate Confirms Acquisition of Lake Masumi
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.58,0:40:42.54,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Construction started at an incredible pace
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.05,0:40:50.51,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,A giant leisure center is being built by Yasuda Conglomerate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.99,0:41:00.43,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Lake Masumi waters are emptied into the Shimozawa Valley
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.40,0:41:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few more days left...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.84,0:41:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Should be done by tomorrow evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.17,0:41:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is Ippei. Right. The day after tomorrow it will be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.70,0:41:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Please arrange an arrest warrant. Yes. Count on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.27,0:41:35.24,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,{To everyone's surprise, }It was established that the entire construction process was initiated on Mr. Yasuda's personal whim of finding a cadaver in the water
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.54,0:41:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.55,0:41:52.09,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,The bottom of the lake revealed a concrete encased body!!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.59,0:41:55.02,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Tenacious investigation pays off!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.29,0:42:00.26,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Kaisei Group young successor Yoichi Toyoda arrested!! \NSuspected of murder \NMistress killer {Lover murder}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.26,0:42:05.27,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,She followed him to death!! {A loving woman fidelity got her murdered!!} \NKaisei Group young successor Yoichi Toyoda arrested on charges of murder!! \N{Irrelevant text on the right: Petition for Leave of Absence... ...was denied...}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.27,0:42:10.02,Sign,SIGN,0,0,0,,Body remains found in the Masumi Lake!!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.11,0:42:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a complete fucking moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.37,0:42:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on. Don't make a lady wait.{Someone is waiting for you over there.} You can go now, go!{It's fine, fine.}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.07,0:42:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{Did it end the way you like it after all?} Are you content with the ultimate conclusion of this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.07,0:43:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thanks to your participation{, I am}.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.67,0:43:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we have its most vital part firmly under control, nothing stays in the way of smashing the Kaisei Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.50,0:43:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a name or a country,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.50,0:43:13.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,Namae mo kuni mo nai
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.67,0:43:18.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Umaretate no genki
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.67,0:43:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The new vigor is being born
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.68,0:43:29.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,All right donna hane wo kureru no
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.68,0:43:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, what kind of feathers can you bestow upon me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.11,0:43:41.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,Bokura wa itsu datte
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.11,0:43:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As fate would have it, we are destined
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.09,0:43:46.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,Kaze wo hiita mama sa
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.09,0:43:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To forever be exposed to cold{wind}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.24,0:43:58.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,Oiru no kireta ashita no puroguramu daiji ni mawashiteru
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.24,0:43:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When I run out of oil, I will carefully turn the page \NFor the program of tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.59,0:44:09.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,Oikakete oikaketemo tsukamenai mono bakari sa
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.59,0:44:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the things I chased, of all the things I'm chasing \NNot a single one is withing my grasp {I still cannot catch any single one}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.58,0:44:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved you, I keep loving you \NBut the closer I get, the less I can see {But I could never see you getting any closer}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.58,0:44:20.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Aishite aishitemo chikazuku hodo mienai
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.77,0:44:43.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Taiyo to hokori no
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.77,0:44:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the sun and the smell of dust
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.68,0:44:48.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nioi wo oboeteru
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.68,0:44:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Are fresh in my memory up to this day
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.67,0:44:59.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,All right donna tane wo maita no
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.67,0:44:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, whichever kind of seeds I sow here
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.26,0:45:11.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,Boku ga kimi ni tsuita
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.26,0:45:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I will keep on walking after you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.19,0:45:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though with all the lies I told that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.19,0:45:17.29,Sign,,0,0,0,,Ano hi no uso yori mo
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.29,0:45:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We will only go{stray} further and further away, \NWithout ever showing a tear
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.29,0:45:28.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,Jouzu ni jouzu ni hagurete yuku \NNamida mo sasowazu ni
